Rating: 3
I made this exactly as instructed and enjoyed it very much. I thought the flavors were great. Then I made it several more times using just whole eggs instead of the more egg white ratio and adding some garlic salt. Even better and even better at room temp. I could see any sort of veggie and spice substitutions could work, but I love oregano in a frittata.

Rating: 3
Clean eating at its best! I've made this twice. The first time, exactly as instructed. Second time with these modifications: used half quantity of potato (I really don't care for potatoes all that much and I'm trying to be low-carb), added about 3 cups of fresh spinach that I sauteed in 1 tsp olive oil in advance and used dill instead of oregano. Who puts oregano on salmon? *lol* Finally, 50 g of goat cheese in dollops on top. EXCELLENT! My only issue is the asparagus which was 'tender crisp'. Perhaps it could go in earlier so that it's cooked through OR I could cut them smaller. In any event, it was delicious!

